FBIS4-5155 "dreas068_c_94003" FBIS-EAS-94-068 Daily Report 8 Apr 1994 North Korea KCNA Reports 6 Apr U.S.-ROK Air Exercise KCNA Reports 6 Apr U.S.-ROK Air Exercise SK0804055194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0528 GMT 8 Apr 94 SK0804055194 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN [Text] Pyongyang, April 8 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialists and the South Korean puppets staged a provocative air war exercise against the North Wednesday with overseas-based KC-135 refueling tankers, F-15 fighter-bombers and AV-8 VTOL [vertical takeoff and landing] assault planes and hundreds of fighter-bombers, assault planes and observation planes belonging to the U.S. Airforce in South Korea and the puppet airforce, military sources said. The air war exercise in the skies above Chongju and Wonju was aimed at testing the capacity of the overseas-based warplanes of the U.S. Airforce and Marines in non-stop quick deployment in the operational airspace and surprise bombing on the North. An overseas-based E-3 early warning plane, two RC-135 strategic reconnaissance planes, U-2 high-attitude strategic reconnaissance plane, RV-1 tactical reconnaissance plane and three RF-4C airforce reconnaissance planes committed an aerial espionage on the frontline area, coastline area, the inland and strategic in-depth areas of the North. Fifteen reconnaissance planes were involved in the aerial espionage on the North in the South Korean airspace that day.
